latestPosts.caption:
When Krishna told Arjuna, “Even on the path of peace, the last door is war,” it struck a deep chord. It was a moment of profound realization, where the illusion of avoiding conflict shattered. Peace is a noble pursuit, but when righteousness is threatened and injustice prevails, war becomes a necessary passage. Arjuna, torn by emotion and duty, was awakened to the truth that peace sometimes demands fierce courage. Krishna’s words were not a call for violence but a call for responsibility - to protect dharma even if it means facing battle. It was peace, defended through strength and resolve.
